Example: Simplified Structure of YouTube
A simplified HTML structure might look like this:
                                                <body>
                                                
                                                <header>
                                                  <!-- logo, search bar, profile -->
                                                </header>
                                                
                                                <div class="container">
                                                
                                                  <aside class="sidebar">
                                                    <!-- home, subscriptions, library -->
                                                  </aside>
                                                
                                                  <main class="videos">
                                                
                                                    <div class="video-card">
                                                      <img>
                                                      <h3>Video title</h3>
                                                      <p>Channel name</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                
                                                    <div class="video-card">
                                                      ...
                                                    </div>
                                                
                                                  </main>
                                                
                                                </div>
                                                
                                                </body>
Key idea:
YouTube repeats the same component many times:
video-card
video-card
video-card
video-card

Each card is built with HTML + CSS + JavaScript.
