Example: Simplified Structure of Amazon
A simplified structure might look like:
                                            <header>
                                              <!-- logo, location, search bar, cart -->
                                            </header>
                                            
                                            <nav>
                                              <!-- category menu -->
                                            </nav>
                                            
                                            <main>
                                            
                                              <section class="product-grid">
                                            
                                                <div class="product-card">
                                                  <img>
                                                  <h3>Product name</h3>
                                                  <p>Price</p>
                                                  <button>Add to Cart</button>
                                                </div>
                                            
                                              </section>
                                            
                                            </main>                                            
                                            <footer>
                                            </footer>
Again, the same product card component repeats hundreds of times.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Modern websites are built using components.
Examples:
Navbar component
Video card component
Product card component
Sidebar component
Footer component

Each component has its own:
HTML structure
CSS styling
JavaScript behavior

Frameworks like:
React
Angular
Vue.js
are designed specifically to build these reusable components.

What the Browser Actually Sees:
When you open a page on YouTube or Amazon, the browser builds something called the DOM (Document Object Model).
Example structure:
                    html
                     └── body
                          ├── header
                          ├── nav
                          ├── main
                          │    ├── div (video card)
                          │    ├── div (video card)
                          │    ├── div (video card)
                          │
                          └── footer

